WEBVTT

00:01.882 --> 00:05.766
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by honeybunny</font>
<font color="#ec14bd">www.addic7ed.com</font>

00:05.886 --> 00:07.854
NARRATOR:
<i>Ahh, Christmas...</i>

00:07.888 --> 00:11.658
<i>That time of year when children</i>
<i>are at their absolute worst.</i>

00:11.692 --> 00:14.227
<i>You see, kids have figured out</i>
<i>that they'll get</i>

00:14.261 --> 00:17.130
<i>whatever they want</i>
<i>whether they're bad or good.</i>

00:17.164 --> 00:20.300
<i>So they all</i>
<i>became spoiled turds.</i>

00:24.471 --> 00:26.306
Hey, I want that.

00:26.340 --> 00:27.807
It's too expensive.

00:27.841 --> 00:29.742
(whining):
But it's Christmas.

00:29.777 --> 00:31.911
I get whatever I want!

00:31.946 --> 00:33.947
If you're a good boy.

00:33.981 --> 00:35.181
Steven Anita!

00:35.215 --> 00:36.950
No, I'm a bad boy.

00:36.984 --> 00:38.351
I get what I want.

00:38.385 --> 00:41.321
♪

00:41.355 --> 00:43.456
What's gotten into
this boy? He's insane.

00:43.490 --> 00:46.726
He's a mystery to me.

00:46.760 --> 00:49.362
♪ I'm the one
they call a mystery ♪

00:49.396 --> 00:51.030
"They"?

00:51.065 --> 00:55.301
♪ I'm the one they call insane

00:55.336 --> 00:58.938
♪ Ain't no other way
I'm meant to be ♪

00:58.973 --> 01:01.107
♪ I want this and gimme that ♪

01:01.141 --> 01:03.576
♪ Are we to blame?
Oh, no ♪

01:03.610 --> 01:05.845
♪ If I told you once,
I told you twice ♪

01:05.879 --> 01:08.047
♪ I'd never be a saint

01:08.082 --> 01:09.048
♪ Daddy, no

01:09.083 --> 01:10.149
♪ Mommy, no

01:10.184 --> 01:12.919
♪ Ain't no saint

01:12.953 --> 01:13.886
♪ Bad

01:13.921 --> 01:17.557
♪ Bad, bad, bad, bad boy

01:17.591 --> 01:20.093
♪ <i>We want it, we want it</i> ♪

01:20.127 --> 01:22.061
<i>♪ And you're paying for it</i>

01:22.096 --> 01:24.564
♪ I'm no good

01:24.598 --> 01:27.033
♪ So bring me toys

01:27.067 --> 01:29.168
♪ <i>I want it, I want it</i> ♪

01:29.203 --> 01:30.870
♪ <i>Don't appreciate it</i> ♪

01:30.904 --> 01:34.073
♪ I know what's coming
and I see the way ♪

01:34.108 --> 01:35.541
♪ <i>He gets whatever he wants ♪</i>

01:35.576 --> 01:37.643
♪ Ain't no other way to go!

01:37.678 --> 01:40.079
♪ <i>Don't you ever tell him no</i> ♪

01:40.114 --> 01:43.082
♪ And when I want it,
you buy it for me ♪

01:43.117 --> 01:45.451
♪ <i>We've got you in our aim</i> ♪

01:45.486 --> 01:47.920
♪ <i>So pony up the dough</i> ♪

01:47.955 --> 01:50.023
(groans)
Steve, you're the worst.

01:50.057 --> 01:51.858
♪ You want the worst?

01:51.892 --> 01:54.093
♪ Well, you gonna see
the worst ♪

01:54.128 --> 01:56.329
♪ 'Cause I'm the best,
the best at bein' the worst! ♪

01:56.363 --> 01:57.563
FRANCINE:
Stop!

01:57.598 --> 02:00.033
I have heard enough
of this song and dance.

02:00.067 --> 02:02.769
You're just lucky I don't beat
you like my dad did to me.

02:02.803 --> 02:06.439
In fact, let's pay
a visit to my dad

02:06.473 --> 02:09.408
so you can see what happens to
naughty boys when they grow up.

02:11.445 --> 02:13.646
Dad, tell him
how much jail sucks.

02:13.680 --> 02:15.515
Tell him about the beatings,
the rapes,

02:15.549 --> 02:18.317
the overly washed
Egyptian cotton bath towels.

02:18.352 --> 02:20.286
Tell him
so he'll stop being bad.

02:20.320 --> 02:22.522
Steve, just be happy
you're bad now

02:22.556 --> 02:24.357
and not when I was boy.

02:24.391 --> 02:26.392
Back then, Krampus
would have come for you.

02:26.427 --> 02:27.627
Krampus?

02:27.661 --> 02:29.395
Yes, Krampus.

02:29.430 --> 02:32.465
The demon of Christmas.

02:32.499 --> 02:34.100
<i>When I was a boy</i>
<i>in Southern Bavaria,</i>

02:34.134 --> 02:36.569
<i>in lower Berchtesgaden,</i>

02:36.603 --> 02:39.338
<i>Santa would ride with Krampus.</i>

02:39.373 --> 02:41.340
<i>Santa would give gifts</i>
<i>to the good kids</i>

02:41.375 --> 02:44.143
<i>and Krampus would punish</i>
<i>the naughty ones.</i>

02:44.178 --> 02:47.180
<i>Scare you</i>
<i>with his rusty chains.</i>

02:47.214 --> 02:49.182
<i>Slap your bottom</i>
<i>with his birch branches.</i>

02:49.216 --> 02:51.084
<i>And if you were really bad,</i>

02:51.118 --> 02:53.319
<i>he'd throw you</i>
<i>in his almost child-sized sack</i>

02:53.353 --> 02:55.321
<i>and shake you good!</i>

02:55.355 --> 02:57.256
<i>Oh, that's Krampus for you.</i>

02:57.291 --> 02:59.358
Yeah, sounds like a
load of bull jizzle.

02:59.393 --> 03:00.793
I've never heard of Krampus.

03:00.828 --> 03:03.830
That's because your gramps
trapped the demon, he did.

03:03.864 --> 03:05.431
<i>On Christmas Eve,</i>

03:05.466 --> 03:08.034
<i>I snuck out of bed</i>
<i>to get more of Mother's strudel</i>

03:08.068 --> 03:10.670
<i>even though she told me</i>
<i>I couldn't have any more.</i>

03:10.704 --> 03:11.971
<i>I didn't care.</i>

03:12.005 --> 03:13.072
<i>I wanted more.</i>

03:13.107 --> 03:14.373
<i>When I got there,</i>

03:14.408 --> 03:16.943
<i>I saw that Krampus</i>
<i>had beat me to it.</i>

03:16.977 --> 03:20.113
<i>He was neck-deep</i>
<i>in Mutter's strudel.</i>

03:20.147 --> 03:22.515
<i>So I trapped him</i>
<i>in that copper pot.</i>

03:22.549 --> 03:24.584
Copper-potted him good.

03:24.618 --> 03:26.652
And that's why you
and all the other baddies

03:26.687 --> 03:30.123
never get a visit
from Krampus on Christmas Eve.

03:30.157 --> 03:31.290
That's nonsense.

03:31.325 --> 03:32.625
See for yourself.

03:32.659 --> 03:35.061
That copper pot is with my stuff
in your basement.

03:35.095 --> 03:36.762
Okay, okay, I'm bored.

03:36.797 --> 03:38.798
Let's go.

03:38.832 --> 03:40.299
Krampus is real.

03:40.334 --> 03:41.734
Real I say!

03:41.768 --> 03:43.102
The copper pot's
in your basement.

03:43.137 --> 03:44.203
It's right there

03:44.238 --> 03:46.439
with my old Rossignol skis!

03:46.473 --> 03:49.041
They're super-long
and super-fast!

03:50.077 --> 03:52.078
Check your basement, Stan!

03:55.182 --> 03:56.716
So, Hayley, have you decided

03:56.750 --> 03:58.151
what to get the family
for Christmas?

03:58.185 --> 04:00.720
(sighs)
No, not yet.

04:00.754 --> 04:03.189
♪ It must be the perfect thing

04:03.223 --> 04:05.258
♪ For a family so loving

04:05.292 --> 04:07.326
♪ A gift that's from above

04:07.361 --> 04:09.929
♪ A gift that's full of love

04:09.963 --> 04:12.231
♪ It's the perfect thing,
can't you see? ♪

04:12.266 --> 04:14.467
♪ A tub of popcorns three

04:14.501 --> 04:16.736
♪ Caramel for Mom,
salted for Dad, ♪

04:16.769 --> 04:19.772
♪ And a hearty cheese
for Steve ♪

04:24.511 --> 04:26.479
♪ Roger, oh, Roger

04:26.513 --> 04:28.614
♪ I hate to be a bother

04:28.649 --> 04:31.384
♪ But I need some money
for a gift ♪

04:31.418 --> 04:34.620
♪ This gift, you see,
is a tub of popcorns three ♪

04:34.655 --> 04:36.422
Wha-Wha-Wha...
just stop, stop.

04:36.456 --> 04:38.191
J-J-Just tell me
what you want.

04:38.225 --> 04:39.592
Wh-What's going on?

04:39.626 --> 04:42.562
I need a job so I can get
the family a Christmas gift.

04:42.596 --> 04:44.197
The bar gets busy
during the holidays.

04:44.231 --> 04:45.665
Maybe you could use
an extra hand.

04:45.699 --> 04:47.066
You're too late, sister.

04:47.100 --> 04:50.536
I already hired college kids
from the water polo team.

04:50.571 --> 04:54.640
I've got almost <i>too</i>
many hands for jobs.

04:54.675 --> 04:56.209
Here's the classifieds.

04:58.145 --> 05:00.613
Ooh, the airport's hiring.

05:00.647 --> 05:02.381
What's with
this Speedo, Jeremy?

05:02.416 --> 05:04.250
It's too baggy.

05:04.284 --> 05:07.086
Is it a tandem Speedo
for two men?

05:08.222 --> 05:09.855
Eh, even this is too loose.

05:09.890 --> 05:11.757
Mark, hop in here!

05:14.294 --> 05:16.395
Did they get this on sale?

05:16.430 --> 05:17.964
Was this the floor model?

05:17.998 --> 05:19.799
Well, if it wasn't, it is now!

05:19.833 --> 05:20.800
Smash!

05:20.834 --> 05:22.235
(gasps)
Steven!

05:22.269 --> 05:23.903
By the power of Grayskull,

05:23.937 --> 05:25.771
what do you think you're doing?

05:25.806 --> 05:27.807
I am hiding these
until Christmas.

05:29.142 --> 05:31.143
Boy driving me insane.

05:31.178 --> 05:33.112
Got me talking like Bernie Mac.

05:40.420 --> 05:42.488
(hollow ringing)

05:42.522 --> 05:44.557
(knock)

05:44.591 --> 05:45.591
Krampus?

05:45.626 --> 05:46.592
Jack?

05:46.627 --> 05:48.628
No, Jack's my dad.

05:48.662 --> 05:51.063
Let... me... out.

05:51.098 --> 05:52.832
I can't. You're a demon.

05:52.866 --> 05:54.233
I-It would be...

05:54.268 --> 05:55.501
unwise.

05:55.535 --> 05:57.737
Release... me.

05:57.771 --> 05:59.038
STEVE:
Hey, bitch!

05:59.072 --> 06:00.806
Where's my Mickey Mouse towel?!

06:00.841 --> 06:02.041
FRANCINE:
I'm sorry!

06:02.075 --> 06:03.542
I'll try harder!

06:03.577 --> 06:05.611
Okay. If I let you out,

06:05.646 --> 06:08.147
will you promise to scare my
son and make him a good boy?

06:08.181 --> 06:09.248
Yeah!

06:09.283 --> 06:11.284
That's, like, exactly
what I do, man.

06:12.419 --> 06:15.121
(screeching)

06:17.324 --> 06:18.391
Ow!

06:18.425 --> 06:19.458
(shouts)
(growls)

06:19.493 --> 06:20.826
(shouts)

06:21.862 --> 06:23.229
No!

06:23.263 --> 06:24.363
Bring me Jack

06:24.398 --> 06:26.732
if you ever want
to see your son again!

06:26.767 --> 06:28.167
Wait!

06:29.336 --> 06:31.937
(screeching)

06:33.544 --> 06:34.996
JACK:
<i>You did</i> what?!

06:35.116 --> 06:36.383
I released Krampus.

06:36.418 --> 06:38.686
I just wanted him to
scare Steve straight.

06:38.720 --> 06:41.755
Sexual orientation
is not a choice!

06:41.790 --> 06:43.324
What?

06:43.358 --> 06:44.992
Look, Krampus took Steve,

06:45.026 --> 06:46.627
and he says he'll only
give him back

06:46.661 --> 06:47.861
if you take his place.

06:47.896 --> 06:49.229
What do you say, Dad?

06:49.231 --> 06:51.599
If I use my CIA connections
to get you out of re,

06:51.633 --> 06:53.300
will you switch with Steve?

07:00.508 --> 07:02.076
I'm in.

07:02.110 --> 07:05.546
Krampus probably took him
to his castle in Bavaria.

07:05.580 --> 07:06.714
I know where it is.

07:06.748 --> 07:08.182
Give me the keys.
I'll drive.

07:08.216 --> 07:09.516
(cackles)

07:09.551 --> 07:11.685
See you, sucker!

07:13.121 --> 07:15.122
(tires screeching)

07:17.058 --> 07:18.025
Yep.

07:18.059 --> 07:20.594
Yeah.
(chuckles)

07:20.629 --> 07:22.696
Uh-huh.
(chuckles)

07:22.731 --> 07:24.365
Yep.

07:25.900 --> 07:26.900
(grunting)

07:26.935 --> 07:27.968
Get off me!

07:28.003 --> 07:29.169
Let me go!

07:29.171 --> 07:30.971
What are you doing?

07:31.006 --> 07:32.039
Krampus is back.

07:32.073 --> 07:33.273
He's been gone for, like,

07:33.308 --> 07:35.476
50 years or something,
you guys.

07:35.510 --> 07:37.344
You can't do this!

07:37.379 --> 07:39.246
I'm an American child!

07:39.280 --> 07:40.414
I'm a treasure!

07:40.448 --> 07:42.449
Well, you in Bavaria now.

07:42.484 --> 07:45.452
(growls)

07:45.487 --> 07:47.621
You need to be punished.

07:47.656 --> 07:50.491
If you lay so much as one
finger on me, I will per...

07:50.525 --> 07:51.992
Who you talking to?

07:52.027 --> 07:53.260
I'm Krampus, bitch!

07:53.294 --> 07:55.129
I do whatever I please.

07:55.163 --> 07:57.398
This is <i>my</i> expertise.

07:57.432 --> 07:59.633
♪ Round the world,
it's all the same ♪

07:59.668 --> 08:02.136
♪ Children freeze
when they hear my name ♪

08:02.170 --> 08:04.171
♪ Krampus, please
don't beat me so ♪

08:04.205 --> 08:06.740
♪ But do I listen? Sadly, no

08:06.775 --> 08:08.876
♪ 80% of kids

08:08.910 --> 08:12.079
♪ End up turnin' into dirtbags

08:12.113 --> 08:15.315
♪ I just laugh

08:15.350 --> 08:17.718
♪ But, Steve, oh, Steve,
you are the worst ♪

08:17.752 --> 08:19.920
♪ Slap that butt
with the branch of birch ♪

08:19.954 --> 08:22.423
♪ Shake them chains
till your ears go numb ♪

08:22.457 --> 08:24.692
♪ See now just
what you've become ♪

08:24.726 --> 08:27.027
♪ Show you that life is pain

08:27.062 --> 08:30.264
♪ Not some silly stupid game

08:30.298 --> 08:32.032
♪ We do it my way

08:33.835 --> 08:37.171
♪ And because you haven't
learned your lesson ♪

08:37.205 --> 08:39.273
♪ You get the rod

08:39.307 --> 08:41.207
♪ You get the rod!

08:41.241 --> 08:43.342
I swear to God,
do not touch me!

08:43.378 --> 08:46.413
You see, Steve, you don't
know anything about pain.

08:46.448 --> 08:47.648
Yes, I do!

08:47.682 --> 08:49.750
Pain is having a girl
named Sheila

08:49.784 --> 08:52.553
walk out on you in the middle
of downtown Baltimore

08:52.587 --> 08:54.021
for some guy named Dennis,

08:54.055 --> 08:57.791
who worked as a mechanic and
made twice as much money as you.

08:57.826 --> 08:59.293
Wha...?
These are things

08:59.327 --> 09:01.128
you know nothing about, boy,

09:01.162 --> 09:03.297
but I'm here to show you.

09:03.331 --> 09:05.332
♪ Agh! Agh!

09:05.366 --> 09:07.801
♪ I'm gonna punish you

09:07.836 --> 09:11.839
♪ You ain't experienced
all that I've been through ♪

09:11.873 --> 09:14.742
♪ Sheila said the kid was mine

09:14.776 --> 09:18.312
♪ But it looked
just like Dennis ♪

09:18.346 --> 09:20.080
♪ That damn Dennis

09:21.449 --> 09:24.752
♪ And because you haven't
learned your lesson ♪

09:24.786 --> 09:26.987
♪ You get the rod
(grunting)

09:27.021 --> 09:29.022
♪ You get the rod!

09:32.060 --> 09:36.363
You'll stay here
until I see Jack.

09:36.397 --> 09:39.266
(sobbing)

09:42.270 --> 09:44.571
Looks like you got
some stuff going on.

09:44.606 --> 09:46.507
Want to tell me what you did?

09:46.541 --> 09:48.375
Want to tell me <i>who</i> you did?

09:48.409 --> 09:49.777
(whispers):
Was it a boy?

09:49.811 --> 09:51.245
Krampus kidnapped Steve.

09:51.279 --> 09:53.514
And the only one who knows
where to find him is Jack.

09:53.548 --> 09:54.615
And Jack took off.

09:54.649 --> 09:55.616
Krampus?

09:55.650 --> 09:57.417
Santa's evil sidekick?

09:57.452 --> 09:58.852
Santa must know where he is.

09:58.887 --> 10:01.221
Santa won't help me.
Santa hates me.

10:01.256 --> 10:04.458
I'm coming for you, Smiths!

10:04.492 --> 10:05.692
Hyah!

10:05.727 --> 10:07.027
(sighs)

10:07.061 --> 10:09.096
Look, even if I wanted
to ask for Santa's help,

10:09.130 --> 10:11.131
how am I supposed to get
to the North Pole?

10:11.166 --> 10:12.766
Oh, boys!

10:17.505 --> 10:19.139
Hyah!

10:19.174 --> 10:21.175
STAN:
Damn...

10:23.344 --> 10:25.913
Santa's village is
behind this wall.

10:27.115 --> 10:29.650
Give me a boost.

10:31.786 --> 10:33.821
Take my hand!

10:38.993 --> 10:41.495
Stan!

10:41.529 --> 10:43.564
(screaming)

10:46.434 --> 10:47.601
(grunting)

10:47.635 --> 10:49.670
Harder.

10:49.704 --> 10:52.072
Way harder.

10:58.112 --> 11:01.348
How dare you come to my house.

11:03.484 --> 11:05.252
Krampus.

11:05.286 --> 11:06.753
What about him?

11:06.788 --> 11:08.789
He's been gone over 50 years.

11:08.823 --> 11:10.257
No, Krampus is alive.

11:10.291 --> 11:12.125
And he has my son.

11:12.160 --> 11:13.927
Who cares about your son?

11:13.962 --> 11:16.029
I can't go back
to sharing Christmas

11:16.064 --> 11:18.165
with that
soul-singing goat.

11:18.199 --> 11:20.434
Always nibbling on my list.

11:20.468 --> 11:21.835
Please, I need your help.

11:21.870 --> 11:23.503
I need to find Steve.

11:23.538 --> 11:25.038
Okay.

11:25.073 --> 11:27.341
I'll help you get your boy

11:27.375 --> 11:31.411
if you help me kill Krampus.

11:32.480 --> 11:33.714
Deal.

11:33.748 --> 11:35.082
Come on, Roger.

11:35.116 --> 11:36.817
Just a little longer.

11:36.851 --> 11:39.286
I'm almost there.

11:40.822 --> 11:42.089
(whimpering)

11:42.123 --> 11:44.658
Aw. Tissue
for your tears?

11:44.692 --> 11:45.893
(yelps)

11:45.927 --> 11:48.128
You don't have to be scared.

11:48.162 --> 11:52.299
Here, refresh yourself
with a cool drink of water.

11:53.334 --> 11:56.069
See, everyone here is nice.

11:56.104 --> 11:57.804
You guys seem okay.

11:57.839 --> 12:00.073
But that Krampus
is a real jerk.

12:00.108 --> 12:01.775
Oh, that's not true!
That's not the way.

12:01.809 --> 12:03.143
(all babbling)

12:03.177 --> 12:05.913
Krampus cares about you
more than anyone.

12:05.947 --> 12:08.849
He cares enough to punish you
when you're bad.

12:08.883 --> 12:11.885
That's cause he's a monster
who enjoys terrorizing kids.

12:11.920 --> 12:14.021
No, no, no, no, no,
you got it all wrong.

12:14.055 --> 12:16.290
Come on.
We'll show you.

12:23.932 --> 12:27.601
♪ With a smack to the forehead

12:27.635 --> 12:31.338
♪ And a poke in the eye

12:31.372 --> 12:35.776
♪ I beaten a lot of children
in my lifetime ♪

12:35.810 --> 12:37.411
♪ Oh, yeah

12:37.445 --> 12:41.548
♪ But the truth
in the matter is ♪

12:41.582 --> 12:45.519
♪ I've been hurtin' inside,
wish I could rewind ♪

12:45.553 --> 12:47.854
♪ Yeah!

12:47.889 --> 12:49.556
♪ Oh

12:49.590 --> 12:50.791
♪ Ooh

12:52.193 --> 12:55.362
♪ When I'm breakin'
their fingers ♪

12:55.396 --> 12:59.199
♪ Lord, it's breakin' my heart

12:59.233 --> 13:04.972
♪ And every Christmas Eve,
my soul is always torn apart ♪

13:05.006 --> 13:06.873
♪ Hey, wait a second, dude

13:06.908 --> 13:08.742
♪ I feel as bad as you

13:08.776 --> 13:11.578
♪ I don't wanna live
like this no more ♪

13:11.612 --> 13:14.014
♪ I just wish I could
start over new ♪

13:14.048 --> 13:17.351
♪ Damn, I feel
just like you do ♪

13:17.385 --> 13:21.088
♪ Oh, I know that
we've been bad ♪

13:21.122 --> 13:25.525
♪ But we don't wanna
be sad no more ♪

13:25.560 --> 13:27.995
♪ Such a drag

13:28.029 --> 13:30.964
♪ 'Cause I miss Mom and Dad

13:30.999 --> 13:34.067
♪ And I miss my baby Sheila

13:34.102 --> 13:35.969
♪ Sheila, why'd you leave?

13:36.004 --> 13:38.105
♪ You left me on my own

13:38.139 --> 13:39.606
